HEADWORD: Saltfoot
<hw>Salt"foot`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A large saltcellar
formerly placed near the center of the table. The superior guests were
seated above the saltfoot.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

